Wash and dry produce.

Halve @grape tomatoes{4%ounce} lengthwise. Pick @parsley{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; finely chop leaves. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Halve @demi-baguette{1} lengthwise.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2.5%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat.

Add tomatoes and cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly charred and slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer tomatoes to a #large bowl{}. Toss with @balsamic glaze{1/2%tsp}, @sugar{1/4%tsp}, a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}. Wipe out pan.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; place between 2 large pieces of #plastic wrap{}. Pound with a #mallet{} or #rolling pin{} until chicken is about ½ inch thick. Season all over with @garlic powder{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in pan used for tomatoes over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} per side.

Remove from heat. Add lemon zest, half the parsley, @butter{1%tablespoon}, a large drizzle of olive oil, and a squeeze of lemon juice. Stir until butter melts, then turn chicken to coat. Transfer chicken to a #cutting board{} and tent with #foil{} to keep warm.

While chicken rests, place baguette halves, cut sides down, in pan used for chicken over medium heat. Cook until golden brown and toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a cutting board. Season cut sides with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{}. Halve on a diagonal.

Add @arugula{2%ounce}, @olive oil{1 1/2%tbsp}, a squeeze of lemon juice, and a big pinch of @salt{pinch} to bowl with tomatoes. Toss to combine.

Divide chicken, salad, and baguette between plates. Top salad with @burrata{4%ounce} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Drizzle plate with as much remaining @balsamic glaze{} as you like. Sprinkle with remaining parsley and serve.